WEBVTT

00:03.208 --> 00:04.440
Helium.

00:04.442 --> 00:06.276
Yes.
Yes.

00:07.479 --> 00:08.244
Taylor Swift.

00:08.246 --> 00:09.379
Yes.

00:11.021 --> 00:11.703
Pi.

00:11.704 --> 00:13.050
Yes.

00:19.224 --> 00:20.323
Kardashian.

00:20.325 --> 00:22.091
More specific.

00:24.929 --> 00:25.962
Khloe?

00:25.964 --> 00:27.297
Yes!

00:27.299 --> 00:28.331
See, I remembered

00:28.333 --> 00:30.066
because if it looks
like Kim it's Kim,

00:30.068 --> 00:31.634
if it looks kind of
like Kim it's Kourtney,

00:31.636 --> 00:33.336
and if it looks nothing
like Kim it's Khloe.

00:33.338 --> 00:34.537
Oh.

00:34.539 --> 00:35.738
Oh,

00:35.740 --> 00:37.774
that's a Venn Diagram,
and I remember because

00:37.776 --> 00:39.108
I thought to myself,

00:39.110 --> 00:41.110
“Venn is he gonna stop
talking about this diagram?”

00:43.181 --> 00:44.781
What are you guys doing?
Oh, well,

00:44.783 --> 00:46.683
we decided to use
our breakfast time

00:46.685 --> 00:49.319
to expand our respective
knowledge bases.

00:49.321 --> 00:50.553
Oh, let me try.

00:50.555 --> 00:52.622
Okay.

00:52.624 --> 00:56.292
Hmm, atom of hydrogen,
Adam of Maroon 5, mic drop.

00:59.197 --> 01:01.297
I'm sorry,
who is Mike Drop?

01:01.299 --> 01:02.598
(chuckles)

01:02.600 --> 01:04.801
Oh, hey, Penny, do you want
to go to the airport

01:04.803 --> 01:06.135
with me later
to pick up my mother?

01:06.137 --> 01:07.170
Sure.
Thanks.

01:07.172 --> 01:08.604
No problem.
Hey, Penny,

01:08.606 --> 01:10.273
um, since you're already
gonna be at the airport,

01:10.275 --> 01:11.441
do I need to go?

01:12.811 --> 01:15.311
Why don't you want to get
your mother from the airport?

01:15.313 --> 01:17.180
Well, I can do without
the 40-minute car ride

01:17.182 --> 01:19.282
where she criticizes
every aspect of my life.

01:19.284 --> 01:22.785
She can cover it
in a car ride?

01:22.787 --> 01:25.688
I could do 40 minutes
on your posture alone.

01:26.624 --> 01:27.890
You really want me to pick up

01:27.892 --> 01:28.891
your mother all by myself?

01:28.893 --> 01:30.626
Hmm, I just feel like

01:30.628 --> 01:32.362
it would be a good chance
for you to bond.

01:32.364 --> 01:33.963
Or a way for you to avoid her?

01:33.965 --> 01:36.265
I don't know what
he's putting on those cards,

01:36.267 --> 01:38.568
but you are smarter than ever.

01:38.570 --> 01:41.738
Fine, if you really want me to,
I will pick your mom up.

01:41.740 --> 01:42.839
Seriously?

01:42.841 --> 01:44.440
Yeah, you know what,
she is my mother-in-law,

01:44.442 --> 01:46.509
and I'd like for us
to have a good relationship.

01:46.511 --> 01:48.444
That is very mature of you,

01:48.446 --> 01:51.280
so I'm gonna go ahead
and say, “Suckah.”

01:51.282 --> 01:54.050
All right, back to learning.
Okay.

01:54.052 --> 01:55.651
(clears throat)

01:55.653 --> 01:57.720
Oh, easy, Bill Nye
the Science Guy.

01:57.722 --> 01:58.955
Or as I know him...

01:58.957 --> 02:01.624
“Creepy old dude
from <i> Dancing with the Stars.”</i>

02:01.626 --> 02:03.092
Ding, ding, ding,
ding, ding!

02:03.094 --> 02:06.729
