02:32.507 --> 02:35.108
Did you guys see there's
an <i> Avengers</i> screening?

02:35.110 --> 02:36.931
Joss Whedon's gonna show
some deleted scenes

02:36.932 --> 02:38.698
and do a question
and answer session.

02:38.700 --> 02:40.633
Oh, well, I have
a few questions for him

02:40.635 --> 02:44.337
about the last <i> Avengers</i> movie...
and a whole lot of answers.

02:44.339 --> 02:47.040
When's the screening?

02:47.042 --> 02:49.042
Uh, it's tonight, but it's
first-come, first-served,

02:49.044 --> 02:51.010
so we should probably get
there early and wait in line.

02:51.012 --> 02:52.979
Let's do it. (chuckles)

02:52.981 --> 02:54.547
Penny's busy with my mother,
so I'm in.

02:54.549 --> 02:56.182
Oh, bad news.

02:56.184 --> 02:58.251
Amy's making me go shopping
with her later,

02:58.253 --> 03:00.653
so looks like none of us can go.

03:02.491 --> 03:05.792
You do realize we're allowed
to have fun without you?

03:05.794 --> 03:08.361
In fact, that's usually
the trick to it.

03:10.031 --> 03:11.798
What time do we
need to get there?

03:11.800 --> 03:13.399
Uh, I'd say by 3:00.

03:13.401 --> 03:15.201
You're really going without me?

03:15.203 --> 03:16.202
It's not a big deal.

03:16.204 --> 03:17.504
Go shopping with Amy,

03:17.506 --> 03:18.905
and we'll save
a spot in line for you.

03:18.907 --> 03:21.975
You don't have the authority
to save places in the line.

03:21.977 --> 03:23.276
If I do that, I'll be cutting.

03:23.278 --> 03:25.111
People do it all the time.

03:25.113 --> 03:26.679
You know the golden rule
of line etiquette:

03:26.681 --> 03:29.149
“No cuts, no buts,
no coconuts.”

03:29.151 --> 03:31.151
If you really
care that much,

03:31.153 --> 03:33.853
there are apps now that'll let
you hire people to do stuff

03:33.855 --> 03:36.022
like errands and
wait in lines.

03:36.024 --> 03:39.192
People are actually
waiting in lines as a job?

03:39.194 --> 03:43.596
Boy, makes me feel better
about my life.

03:43.598 --> 03:45.598
Some of these guys make
over $20 an hour.

03:45.600 --> 03:47.901
And now I feel worse again.

03:50.172 --> 03:53.506
I'm not surprised Leonard
chose to avoid picking me up.

03:53.508 --> 03:57.510
He's battled intimacy issues
his whole life.

03:57.512 --> 04:01.047
Does he have difficulty
maintaining erections?

04:01.049 --> 04:03.383
Wow.
(clears throat)

04:03.385 --> 04:05.351
Didn't even make it
out of the parking lot.

04:06.454 --> 04:07.854
Uh, you know what,
enough about Leonard.

04:07.856 --> 04:09.122
Let's talk about you.

04:09.124 --> 04:10.890
What would you like to
do while you're here?

04:10.892 --> 04:12.792
Dear, I'm a psychiatrist.

04:12.794 --> 04:15.795
You don't have to avoid having
intimate conversations with me.

04:15.797 --> 04:19.199
Well, I'd actually like
for us to be close,

04:19.201 --> 04:21.166
but maybe we start
with our favorite books

04:21.168 --> 04:23.770
and work our way up
to my husband's sex organs.

04:25.674 --> 04:26.973
Very well.

04:26.975 --> 04:28.141
What's the last book
you read?

04:28.143 --> 04:31.845
Um, does <i> Pottery Barn,</i>
<i>Spring</i> count?

04:33.949 --> 04:36.916
Penny, it's only natural to want
your mother-in-law to like you,

04:36.918 --> 04:40.086
and I acknowledge I can be
an intimidating person.

04:40.088 --> 04:43.823
So what can I do to make
this process easier for you?

04:43.825 --> 04:45.124
Uh, for starters,

04:45.126 --> 04:47.260
maybe you can not psychoanalyze
everything I say?

04:47.262 --> 04:49.596
And how does it
make you feel

04:49.598 --> 04:52.665
when I psychoanalyze
everything you say?

04:52.667 --> 04:55.034
Uncomfortable.

04:55.036 --> 04:56.302
That was a joke, dear.

04:56.304 --> 04:57.871
Oh. Sorry.

04:57.873 --> 04:59.672
(chuckles)
Didn't know you made those.

05:01.376 --> 05:03.109
Hey, listen, what
if we have a little

05:03.111 --> 05:06.112
mother-in-law-daughter-in-law
dinner tonight?

05:06.114 --> 05:08.147
So just the two of us?

05:08.149 --> 05:10.683
Or I invite a few girlfriends,

05:10.685 --> 05:12.085
'cause hearing you say
“the two of us”

05:12.087 --> 05:14.354
just sent a chill
right down my spine.

05:16.858 --> 05:18.858
(car door opens)

05:18.860 --> 05:20.860
Hey.

05:20.862 --> 05:22.295
What are you doing here?

05:22.297 --> 05:23.296
You're not Sheldon.

05:23.298 --> 05:26.165
I thought that might come up.

05:27.302 --> 05:29.302
Sheldon hired me to go
shopping with you.

05:29.304 --> 05:31.204
Hold on.

05:31.206 --> 05:34.240
He paid you to get out
of spending time with me?

05:34.242 --> 05:36.542
No, it's not like that.

05:36.544 --> 05:39.312
There's a long line
he'd rather stand in.

05:40.949 --> 05:42.649
So what are we doing?
Old Navy, Build-A-Bear?

05:42.651 --> 05:44.250
I get paid either way.

05:46.321 --> 05:48.354
We're not going
shopping together.

05:48.356 --> 05:50.356
You sure?
I'm happy to hold your bag.

05:50.358 --> 05:53.293
And Sheldon gave me money
for a hotdog on a stick.

05:54.829 --> 05:57.230
Can you understand why
I might be annoyed right now?

05:57.232 --> 06:01.234
(chuckles) Look, lady,
I just work here.

06:03.705 --> 06:07.540
We've waited in a lot of
lines together, haven't we?

06:07.542 --> 06:09.108
Remember when we camped out

06:09.110 --> 06:10.777
for the <i> Doctor Who</i> panel
at Comic-Con?

06:10.779 --> 06:12.779
Yeah, sleeping under the
stars with other fans

06:12.781 --> 06:14.480
who love the show
as much as we do.

06:14.482 --> 06:17.717
Waking up, wondering which one
of those fans stole our wallets.

06:18.720 --> 06:21.454
SHELDON: Stuart,
what are you doing here?

06:21.456 --> 06:23.423
Sheldon, you are the most
inconsiderate person

06:23.425 --> 06:26.326
I have ever met
in my entire life!

06:27.529 --> 06:29.028
Where do you get off sending me

06:29.030 --> 06:31.230
to shop with your girlfriend?!

06:31.232 --> 06:32.532
I don't understand.

06:32.534 --> 06:34.033
You were happy to do this
when I hired you.

06:34.035 --> 06:35.635
Why-why are you
upset with me now?

06:35.637 --> 06:38.972
Oh, I'm not upset with you, but
Amy's pretty bent out of shape,

06:38.974 --> 06:43.276
so she hired me
to let you have it.

06:44.879 --> 06:47.046
Well, I suppose
turnabout is fair play.

06:47.048 --> 06:49.983
You're darn right it's fair
play, you selfish jerk!

06:54.089 --> 06:55.355
You know, just when I think

06:55.357 --> 06:56.889
we're making progress
in our relationship,

06:56.891 --> 06:58.524
we revert to our old patterns

06:58.526 --> 07:00.226
where thoughts and feelings
go unexpressed.

07:00.228 --> 07:01.894
I mean, if he didn't want
to go shopping with me,

07:01.896 --> 07:03.363
why didn't he just say so?

07:03.365 --> 07:07.266
Maybe he couldn't get
a word in edgewise.

07:09.904 --> 07:11.938
I'm sorry, I've been
going on and on.

07:11.940 --> 07:13.573
Oh, it's all right, dear.

07:13.575 --> 07:16.542
Sheldon has a brilliant
and complicated mind.

07:16.544 --> 07:19.579
It's understandable that being
in a relationship with him

07:19.581 --> 07:20.813
could be trying.

07:20.815 --> 07:22.248
I called him “babe” once.

07:22.250 --> 07:25.051
He asked me to get a drug test.

07:26.621 --> 07:28.521
Well, I do admire your resolve.

07:28.523 --> 07:31.157
You're an extraordinary woman.
Thank you.

07:31.159 --> 07:33.526
You know, she's
my mother-in-law.

07:33.528 --> 07:35.261
Why can't I bond
with her like that?

07:35.263 --> 07:38.664
Amy's with Sheldon
who she loves like a son.

07:38.666 --> 07:40.500
You're with her son...

07:40.502 --> 07:43.269
who she doesn't.

07:43.271 --> 07:46.305
Do you realize it took me five
years to get a massage from him?

07:46.307 --> 07:49.976
Oh, well, that still could be
a big step for Sheldon.

07:49.978 --> 07:51.978
Three minutes.

07:51.980 --> 07:54.981
And he used a kitchen timer.

07:54.983 --> 07:57.417
I felt like a soft-boiled egg.

07:58.920 --> 08:00.920
You know, being in a
relationship with Leonard

08:00.922 --> 08:03.056
also comes
with its challenges.

08:03.058 --> 08:04.390
Yes.

08:04.392 --> 08:07.760
Well, what can you do?

08:07.762 --> 08:09.729
(knocking on door)

08:11.232 --> 08:13.299
Maybe it's Sheldon,
here to say he's sorry.

08:13.301 --> 08:16.135
Sheldon says he's sorry.

08:19.107 --> 08:21.374
Bernadette, I'll give you
five dollars to slam the door.

08:21.376 --> 08:22.975
I would have done
it for three.

