Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

08:32.792 --> 08:35.426
Boy, all this standing's
making me tired.

08:35.428 --> 08:39.296
Good thing I brought
my collapsible stick chair.

08:39.298 --> 08:41.899
Not the stick chair.

08:41.900 --> 08:43.667
You look like an idiot
on that thing.

08:43.669 --> 08:46.036
Sticks and stones
may break my bones,

08:46.038 --> 08:48.939
but chairs on sticks
are comfy.

08:49.809 --> 08:51.542
Hey.
Hey.

08:51.544 --> 08:53.711
Is everything
smoothed out with Amy?

08:53.713 --> 08:55.579
Uh, no, she's still pretty mad.

08:55.581 --> 08:58.916
Did you make the apology
as sincere as I would have?

08:58.918 --> 09:01.552
I said,
“Sheldon says he's sorry.”

09:01.554 --> 09:04.455
Oh, well, that's
laying it on a little thick.

09:06.392 --> 09:09.126
You think it's time you
apologize to her yourself?

09:09.128 --> 09:10.694
(sighs)
I suppose so.

09:10.696 --> 09:12.585
But if I get out of the line,
I'll lose my spot.

09:12.586 --> 09:15.186
I'm happy to hold your place
till you get back.

09:15.188 --> 09:16.488
You would do that?

09:16.490 --> 09:18.857
Consider it my way
of getting more of your money.

09:19.993 --> 09:22.727
You're a good man.

09:23.864 --> 09:25.497
So, Beverly,
did you know Penny

09:25.499 --> 09:27.165
is the number
three sales rep

09:27.167 --> 09:28.767
at our pharmaceutical company?

09:28.769 --> 09:30.802
Oh, I didn't realize
you two work together.

09:30.804 --> 09:32.137
Well, we don't exactly.

09:32.139 --> 09:34.272
I'm a microbiologist
for the research team.

09:34.274 --> 09:35.774
Oh, what are you
currently developing?

09:35.776 --> 09:37.809
Some exciting new
anti-anxiety drugs.

09:37.811 --> 09:39.110
That's interesting.

09:39.112 --> 09:42.213
I just attended a lecture
on pediatric anxiety.

09:42.215 --> 09:44.716
Oh, was it, uh,
Dr. Jenofski?

09:44.718 --> 09:45.784
I just saw
his TED Talk!

09:45.786 --> 09:47.018
BEVERLY:
It was.

09:47.020 --> 09:48.653
Let's get back to Penny.

09:48.655 --> 09:49.954
Hey, weren't you telling me

09:49.956 --> 09:51.489
something great
about your company car?

09:51.491 --> 09:52.957
Um...

09:52.959 --> 09:55.026
(clears her throat)

09:55.028 --> 09:58.663
It has seat warmers.

09:58.665 --> 10:00.799
(knocking at door)

10:00.801 --> 10:02.600
SHELDON:
Amy! Amy!

10:02.602 --> 10:04.302
Amy!
Come in.

10:04.304 --> 10:05.937
Hello, everyone.

10:05.939 --> 10:07.339
Oh, Beverly, good to see you!

10:07.341 --> 10:09.107
I'd love to chat,
but there's a line

10:09.109 --> 10:10.975
that could start moving
any minute, so let's do this.

10:10.977 --> 10:12.110
Amy?

10:12.112 --> 10:14.045
A proper apology
requires three steps.

10:14.047 --> 10:16.247
Step one--
an admission of wrongdoing.

10:16.249 --> 10:18.183
Amy, I was wrong.
Step two--

10:18.185 --> 10:20.318
a promise never
to repeat said action.

10:20.320 --> 10:23.021
Amy, that action will never be
repeated, and that's a promise.

10:23.023 --> 10:25.523
Step three-- an earnest request
for forgiveness.

10:25.525 --> 10:26.791
Amy, I hope you can forgive me.

10:26.793 --> 10:28.059
And I hope you
do it right now,

10:28.061 --> 10:29.427
'cause there's an Uber
waiting downstairs,

10:29.429 --> 10:31.062
and I don't want to repeat
this apology nonsense

10:31.064 --> 10:33.198
with my driver Ganesh.

10:34.434 --> 10:36.735
Fine.

10:36.737 --> 10:38.336
Oh, thanks!
You're a peach!

10:38.338 --> 10:39.537
Beverly, we'll
catch up soon.

10:39.539 --> 10:40.839
Bernadette, it was
a pleasure as always,

10:40.841 --> 10:42.407
Penny, you have
spinach in your teeth.

10:42.409 --> 10:44.442
(door closes)

10:44.444 --> 10:47.746
How long have I had spinach
in my teeth?

10:47.748 --> 10:49.214
Since the airport, dear.

10:52.486 --> 10:56.254
You look like you come
with a kickstand.

10:56.256 --> 10:58.556
You can't make me feel bad.

10:58.558 --> 11:00.859
Hmm, maybe not. Leonard?

11:00.861 --> 11:03.728
So, when the aliens
brought you back,

11:03.730 --> 11:06.097
they just left the probe in?

11:07.067 --> 11:09.000
I'm back.

11:09.002 --> 11:10.969
Hey, how'd it go?
It went well.

11:10.971 --> 11:12.804
Yeah, I've learned that
if you never say you're sorry,

11:12.806 --> 11:16.408
the times you do really
puts them on their heels.

11:16.410 --> 11:18.977
Uh, Stuart, I relieve you
of your line duties.

11:18.979 --> 11:21.279
Anyone else need
anything before I go?

11:21.281 --> 11:24.282
I'll give you a dollar
if make fun of Raj.

11:24.284 --> 11:26.751
That's mean.
Five.

11:26.753 --> 11:29.320
You look like Tigger
if Tigger looked like a jackass.

11:31.358 --> 11:33.391
Uh, if you ever need
a reference or anything,

11:33.393 --> 11:35.460
just let me know.

11:35.462 --> 11:37.061
Hey, guys.

11:37.063 --> 11:38.263
WOMAN:
You made it.

11:38.265 --> 11:40.465
Did you see that?

11:40.467 --> 11:42.634
He just cut the line.

11:42.636 --> 11:44.235
He's just joining
his friends; it's fine.

11:44.237 --> 11:45.804
(stammers)
No, it's not fine.

11:45.806 --> 11:48.106
It is a breach
of line etiquette.

11:48.108 --> 11:49.574
We're near the front
of the line.

11:49.576 --> 11:50.975
We'll get in either way.

11:50.977 --> 11:52.877
What if every person in front
of us lets someone cut?

11:52.879 --> 11:53.417
We'd still get in.

11:53.421 --> 11:55.380
What if each of those people
let someone cut?

11:55.382 --> 11:56.065
Still get in.

11:56.089 --> 11:57.550
But then each of those
people let someone cut?

11:57.551 --> 11:59.484
We'd still get in,
but first I'd hit you

11:59.486 --> 12:01.786
over the head
with his stick chair.

12:03.824 --> 12:05.490
Excuse me.
Oh, please don't.

12:05.492 --> 12:07.725
Uh, uh, I couldn't
help but notice

12:07.727 --> 12:09.461
that you cut the line.

12:09.463 --> 12:10.728
Oh, uh, I'm with my friends.

12:10.730 --> 12:11.729
It's cool.

12:11.731 --> 12:12.931
Well, no.

12:12.933 --> 12:14.466
It's not cool.

12:14.468 --> 12:16.801
If there were
reserved seating,

12:16.803 --> 12:18.703
and we all had tickets,
that would be fine.

12:18.705 --> 12:20.138
But this line is
first-come, first-served.

12:20.140 --> 12:22.540
Not “show up tardy and
nevertheless be first served”.

12:22.542 --> 12:23.808
Right here.

12:23.810 --> 12:26.010
No.

12:27.781 --> 12:29.414
You need to go to
the back of the line.

12:29.416 --> 12:32.250
(scoffs)
Uh, who made you line monitor?

12:32.252 --> 12:35.220
Mrs. Wunch in fourth grade.

12:36.289 --> 12:37.889
And my slogan was
“a line that's straight

12:37.891 --> 12:40.058
is a line that's great”"

12:41.228 --> 12:42.794
Is this guy for real?

12:42.796 --> 12:46.464
Boy, I wish
I could say no.

12:47.601 --> 12:50.502
That was very nice
of Sheldon to apologize.

12:50.504 --> 12:52.604
Well, he's come a long way.

12:52.606 --> 12:55.206
Or a short way very slowly,

12:55.208 --> 12:58.643
so it feels like a long way.

12:58.645 --> 13:01.346
Your relationship
with him is fascinating.

13:01.348 --> 13:04.282
I'm preparing to write a book
on high-achieving couples,

13:04.284 --> 13:06.217
and I would love to
interview the both of you.

13:06.219 --> 13:07.619
Oh, sure.

13:07.621 --> 13:09.420
I'll-I'll talk
to Sheldon about it.

13:09.422 --> 13:11.489
You know, Bernadette's husband
is a former astronaut.

13:11.491 --> 13:13.258
Really?

13:13.260 --> 13:14.359
Do you think
he would be interested

13:14.361 --> 13:15.593
in being interviewed
as well?

13:15.595 --> 13:17.128
Do I think he'd be interested?

13:17.130 --> 13:19.030
Sometimes I hear him
pretending to be interviewed

13:19.032 --> 13:20.999
when he's alone
in the bathroom.

13:21.001 --> 13:23.001
Wonderful!

13:23.003 --> 13:25.270
I'll give you
my contact information.

13:26.373 --> 13:29.474
Um, you should probably
talk to Penny, too.

13:29.476 --> 13:32.744
About what?

13:33.680 --> 13:34.712
Okay, you know what?

13:34.714 --> 13:36.314
This is ridiculous.

13:36.316 --> 13:37.448
I've been trying to make

13:37.450 --> 13:38.583
a connection with you all day,

13:38.585 --> 13:39.851
and clearly I'm getting nowhere.

13:39.853 --> 13:41.953
Well, are you
seeking a connection

13:41.955 --> 13:44.589
or just some form of validation?

13:44.591 --> 13:47.225
What I was seeking was
some sort of friendship.

13:47.227 --> 13:49.794
But at this point, I'll take you
not insulting me to my face.

13:49.796 --> 13:52.130
My intention was never
to insult you.

13:52.132 --> 13:53.498
You've been doing it all day!

13:53.500 --> 13:55.199
Do you even know
what an insult is?!

13:55.201 --> 13:57.168
Well, it's not a clinical term.

13:57.170 --> 13:59.871
But one example would be
your marrying my son,

13:59.873 --> 14:01.573
and not inviting me
or even telling me

14:01.575 --> 14:03.374
the wedding was taking place.

14:06.112 --> 14:08.379
Okay, good example.

14:11.851 --> 14:14.986
What about Joss Whedon's work
makes you think he'd be okay

14:14.988 --> 14:17.021
with rule-breakers
and line-cutters?!

14:17.023 --> 14:18.823
The Avengers are rule-breakers!

14:18.825 --> 14:21.893
Being vengeful is in
their job description!

14:21.895 --> 14:24.662
They work for SHIELD,

14:24.664 --> 14:26.898
which is a sanctioned department
of the U.S. Government!

14:26.900 --> 14:28.566
Do you work for a
sanctioned department

14:28.568 --> 14:30.301
of the U.S. Government?

14:30.303 --> 14:31.736
As a matter of fact I do.

14:31.738 --> 14:35.340
At a little place
called the DMV.

14:36.743 --> 14:37.875
He's got him there.

14:37.877 --> 14:41.479
The D even stands
for department.

14:41.481 --> 14:42.680
Excuse me!

14:42.682 --> 14:43.781
Excuse me,
can I please

14:43.783 --> 14:45.183
see a show of hands?

14:45.185 --> 14:47.819
Who here takes issue with
this person cutting the line?

14:49.589 --> 14:52.056
Told you.

14:52.058 --> 14:54.325
Well, what a sad
state of affairs!

14:54.327 --> 14:56.194
That you've all been
so ground down

14:56.196 --> 14:58.830
by life, you don't even notice
when someone disrespects you.

14:58.832 --> 15:00.465
I can't believe
we're gonna get beat up,

15:00.467 --> 15:04.035
and it's not
because of your chair.

15:04.037 --> 15:06.337
You know, right now,
at the back of this line,

15:06.339 --> 15:08.006
there's a movie fan
like you

15:08.008 --> 15:09.440
who's not going to get in,

15:09.442 --> 15:11.809
because this person
simply doesn't care.

15:11.811 --> 15:13.277
Yeah, well, 61 years ago,

15:13.279 --> 15:15.413
there was another person
at the back of the line

15:15.415 --> 15:17.715
and her name
was Rosa Parks.

15:20.787 --> 15:23.021
Okay, you may have
to pretend you're black

15:23.023 --> 15:26.257
to get us out of here.

15:26.259 --> 15:28.726
Now, let's follow in that
brave woman's footsteps,

15:28.728 --> 15:31.029
and stand up for ourselves!

15:31.031 --> 15:33.531
And-and I realize that she
stood up by remaining seated,

15:33.533 --> 15:35.867
but now is not that time
to enjoy the irony of that.

15:35.869 --> 15:37.435
Now, I ask you again.

15:37.437 --> 15:39.604
Who here takes issue
with this person--?

15:39.606 --> 15:41.739
Why should we listen to you?
You cut the line yourself.

15:41.741 --> 15:44.042
I most certainly did not.

15:44.044 --> 15:45.810
I saw you.

15:45.812 --> 15:48.146
If you're feeling dizzy,

15:48.148 --> 15:50.848
it's because the tables
have turned.

15:52.652 --> 15:56.020
Excuse me, I paid someone
to wait in line for me,

15:56.022 --> 15:57.689
and then
when I arrived,

15:57.691 --> 15:59.490
he left, so what you
saw, my good woman,

15:59.492 --> 16:02.026
was “swapsies”,
not “cutsies”.

16:02.028 --> 16:03.361
Oh, no, no, no, no, wait!

16:03.363 --> 16:04.829
I ask you all again.
A show of hands.

16:04.831 --> 16:06.698
Who here takes issue--?
Well, stop moving!

16:06.700 --> 16:07.665
He's gonna get in!

16:07.667 --> 16:08.933
Buddy, let it go.
No, I can't.

16:08.935 --> 16:10.068
This isn't right.

16:10.070 --> 16:11.135
You did everything you could.

16:11.137 --> 16:13.705
No, I could've done more.

16:13.707 --> 16:16.207
Now, now, you
denigrated the memory

16:16.209 --> 16:17.875
of a great civil
rights pioneer.

16:17.877 --> 16:19.310
That's all anyone could ask.

16:22.348 --> 16:26.350
To be honest, I'm surprised you
cared about the wedding at all.

16:26.352 --> 16:28.286
I'm still human, Penny.

16:28.288 --> 16:30.254
Not getting invited
to my own son's wedding

16:30.256 --> 16:32.190
is difficult to ignore.

16:32.192 --> 16:33.591
AMY:
I know how you feel.

16:33.593 --> 16:35.493
She didn't invite any of us.

16:35.495 --> 16:37.195
It was spur of the moment!

16:37.197 --> 16:40.064
But we did get to see a live
stream of it on the Internet.

16:40.066 --> 16:42.600
I could've watched it
on the Internet?

16:44.170 --> 16:46.804
Thank you.

16:47.974 --> 16:50.641
So if we would have asked you
to come to Vegas

16:50.643 --> 16:53.010
to see us get married,
you would've come?

16:53.012 --> 16:55.980
No, I would've said
you're making a huge mistake.

16:55.982 --> 16:58.916
But an invitation
would've been nice.

16:58.918 --> 17:02.687
You really think
we made a mistake?

17:02.689 --> 17:04.321
At the time I did.

17:04.324 --> 17:06.691
But I-I've never seen
Leonard so happy,

17:06.693 --> 17:09.460
so... perhaps I was wrong.

17:09.462 --> 17:11.561
Wow.

17:11.564 --> 17:13.564
Okay.

17:13.566 --> 17:15.465
Well, um, how about this?

17:15.468 --> 17:16.968
Maybe while
you're still in town,

17:16.970 --> 17:19.871
Leonard and I could have
another small ceremony.

17:19.873 --> 17:22.106
You know, if you're interested.

17:22.108 --> 17:25.710
I would find that
perfectly acceptable.

17:25.712 --> 17:27.612
(gasps) She would find it

17:27.614 --> 17:29.013
perfectly acceptable!

17:29.015 --> 17:31.215
You guys saw it! We bonded!

17:42.838 --> 17:44.104
Howie?

17:44.106 --> 17:46.139
You doing okay?
You've been in there a while.

17:46.141 --> 17:48.375
WOLOWITZ: (stammers)
I'm fine. Be right out.

17:50.512 --> 17:53.480
Am I an American hero?
(chuckles)

17:55.050 --> 17:57.884
Well, that's
a good question, Jim.

17:57.886 --> 18:01.788
Don't you think once
an astronaut leaves the planet,

18:01.790 --> 18:05.158
he's a hero to all the nations
of the Earth?

18:05.160 --> 18:08.628
(toilet flushes)

18:08.630 --> 18:10.330
Okey dokey.

18:10.332 --> 18:11.973
I think I have time
for one more question.

